# graphify — exclude non-semantic image assets from the documentation knowledge graph.
#
# Why: the doc corpus under docs/ contains 260+ screenshots (docs/analysis/shots/**)
# and program mockups. graphify has no vision pass configured here, so these images
# carry no extractable text — yet every incremental run re-stats them and, because
# most were added after the last manifest was written, flags ~200 of them as
# "changed". That manifest churn (a) makes `detect_incremental` report hundreds of
# phantom doc changes and (b) would make a `--mode deep` run try to LLM-process every
# screenshot. Excluding images makes the doc graph markdown-focused and keeps the
# incremental gate honest — it then reports only real .md changes.
#
# gitignore semantics (unanchored patterns match at any depth under docs/).
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.webp
*.svg
